column28:
The purpose of this study is to understand how people imagine others. In particular, we are interested in how people perceive others when they are acting violently. Following this page, you will be asked to read a story about an act of violence. If you are uncomfortable with this, you should not participate in this study. This study should only take about 3 minutes. 

 

NOTE - You will be asked 2 simple questions about the content of the story to ensure that you've read it. These questions are very easy if you read the story.

If you do not answer the 2 content questions correctly, your HIT may be rejected. 



Make sure you are not distracted when taking this survey. When you are ready, please click the box below.

column70: We appreciate your participation. Do you have any comments about this study?

this was a really weird one

The demographic questions about sex and gender are unclear.  You don't distinguish between biological sex and gender and do not give options for intersex, non-binary, or transgender people.  Those folks either can't complete your survey or will fudge their answers to fit the available options, which isn't good for your data.
This was very interesting. Thank you.

This was a very interesting story that I had to imagine.
